*****HTML Important Topics

HTML (HyperText Markup Language)
  Standard language used to create the structure of web pages.
Tag
  Basic building block of HTML used to define elements like <p>, <div>, etc.
Element 
  A complete HTML structure including opening tag, content, and closing tag.
Attribute 
  Extra information added to HTML elements like class, id, or href.
Heading Tags (<h1>–<h6>) 
  Used to define headings with different sizes and importance.
Paragraph (<p>) 
  Used to define a block of text.
Anchor Tag (<a>) 
  Used to create hyperlinks to other pages or resources.
Image Tag (<img>) 
  Used to display images on a webpage.
List (<ul>, <ol>, <li>) 
  Used to create ordered and unordered lists.
Table (<table>) 
  Used to display data in rows and columns.
Form (<form>) 
  Used to collect user input.
Input (<input>) 
  Used to create input fields in forms.
Div (<div>) 
  Block-level container used for layout and grouping elements.
Span (<span>) 
  Inline container used to style or group text.
Semantic Tags 
  Tags like <header>, <footer> that describe meaning of content.


*****JavaScript Important Topics

JavaScript 
  Programming language used to make web pages interactive.
Variable 
  Used to store data values using var, let, or const.
Data Types 
  Types of data like number, string, boolean, object, etc.
Function 
  Block of code designed to perform a specific task.
Operator 
  Symbols used to perform operations like +, -, ==, etc.
Conditional Statements 
  Used to make decisions using if, else, switch.
Loop 
  Used to repeat code multiple times like for, while.
Array 
  Collection of multiple values stored in a single variable.
Object 
  Collection of key-value pairs representing real-world entities.
DOM (Document Object Model) 
  Interface to access and manipulate HTML using JavaScript.
Event 
  Action like click, hover, or keypress detected by JavaScript.
Event Listener 
  Method to handle events like addEventListener().
String 
  Sequence of characters used to represent text.
Boolean 
  Data type with only two values: true or false.
Scope 
  Defines where variables can be accessed in code.
Callback Function 
  Function passed as an argument to another function.
Arrow Function 
  Short syntax for writing functions using =>.
JSON (JavaScript Object Notation) 
  Format for storing and exchanging data.
Map() 
  Creates a new array by applying a function to each element.
Filter() 
  Returns a new array with elements that pass a condition.
Reduce() 
  Reduces an array to a single value using a function.
forEach() 
  Executes a function on each array element.
find() 
  Returns the first element that matches a condition.
some() 
  Checks if at least one element satisfies a condition.
every() 
  Checks if all elements satisfy a condition.
Template Literals 
  Use backticks ( ) for string interpolation.
Destructuring 
  Extract values from arrays/objects into variables.
Spread Operator (...) 
  Expands elements of arrays/objects.
Rest Operator (...) 
  Collects multiple values into a single array.
Closures 
  Function that remembers its outer scope.
Hoisting 
  Variables and functions are moved to top before execution.
Promises 
  Handle async operations with resolve/reject.
Async/Await 
  Cleaner way to write asynchronous code.
Fetch API 
  Used to make HTTP requests to servers.
LocalStorage 
  Stores data in browser permanently.
SessionStorage 
  Stores data temporarily for session.
SetTimeout() 
  Executes code after a delay.
SetInterval() 
  Executes code repeatedly at intervals.
Error Handling (try...catch) 
  Handles runtime errors safely.
Modules (import/export) 
  Split code into reusable files.
Class 
  Blueprint for creating objects (OOP concept).